<p>I'm also going to add a note: this is <em>not</em> needed for persistence, but it might
save you from an edge-case bug. Suppose we called <code>$genus-&gt;addGenusScientist()</code>
to link a <code>User</code> to the <code>Genus</code>. Then later, during the <em>same</em> request - that's
important - we have that same <code>User</code> object, and we call <code>getStudiedGenuses()</code>. We
would want the <code>Genus</code> that was just linked to be in that collection. This does that!
We're guaranteeing that both sides of the relationship stay synchronized.</p>
<p>Do the same thing down in the remover: <code>$user-&gt;removeStudiedGenus($this)</code>:</p>
